The article discusses the joint statement issued by the United States, Chile, Poland, Nigeria, Morocco, Thailand, and the Republic of Korea regarding their efforts to promote nuclear security and prevent nuclear terrorism. These countries hosted regional outreach meetings to discuss nuclear security challenges in their respective regions. The United States and the Republic of Korea also organized informational meetings at the International Atomic Energy Agency and the United Nations as part of their outreach efforts. The statement emphasizes the importance of continuing these outreach efforts as they work towards implementing the 2010 and 2012 Nuclear Security Communique and prepare for the 2014 Nuclear Security Summit.